body: Which of the following correctly describes a yazoo stream?

choices.W: A stream that lies on the floodplain of another river, running parallel to said river
choices.X: A stream created by the confluence of two other streams
choices.Y: A stream originating from the ocean
choices.Z: A stream that drains into a basin with no outlet

answer: W) A STREAM THAT LIES ON THE FLOODPLAIN OF ANOTHER RIVER RUNNING PARALLEL TO SAID RIVER
